quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  15,71,"He said, 'These are my daughters, (for marriage) if you are to do so.""
  15,72,"By your life, (0 prophet) they are wandering blindly in their intoxication (misguidance)."
  15,73,"So, they were seized by the Cry at sunrise."
  15,74,"Then, We turned it (the city) upside down and sent over them rain of stones made of clay."
  15,75,"Surely, in that there are signs for those who read signs."
  15,76,"And surely, it (their city) is located on the straight road."
  15,77,"Surely, in it there are signs for the believers."
  15,78,"And, indeed, the people of Aikah were transgressors."
  15,79,"So, We punished them in retribution and both of them are (situated) by a highway, clearly visible."
  15,80,"And the people of Al-Hijr did belie the messengers."
  15,81,"And We provided them with Our signs yet they kept turning away from them."
  15,82,"They would hew out houses from the hills, in peace."
  15,83,"Then, the Cry seized them by the morning."
  15,84,"So, whatever they earned did not come to their help."
  15,85,"And We did not create the heavens and the earth and whatever is there in between them but with truth. And the Hour is sure to come. Therefore, overlook in a gracious manner."
  15,86,"Surely, your Lord is the Master - Creator, the All-Knowing."
  15,87,"And We have given you the seven oft-repeated verses and the glorious Qur’ an."
  15,88,"Never stretch your eyes to-wards what We have given to groups of them to enjoy and do not grieve for them, and be kind to believers in humbleness."
  15,89,"And say, 'Z am the one who warns clearly (against punishment)"
  15,90,"as We sent down upon the schismatics"